data.text:
Kibbutz Ramot Menashe is located in the north of Israel on the Menashe plateau between the Carmel mountain range and the Jezreel Valley. The main source of Ramot Menashe’s profits comes from industrial activity, while some agricultural sectors are active, such as cowsheds, Avocado groves and field crops. Tourism and entertainment are also developed in the kibbutz.

Photo: Kibbutz Ramot Menashe
